Recommended Flow
1. Create Infrastructure
Create EC2-1 → Jenkins Master  (Usercreation using useradd, Install Jenkins, Java)
Create EC2-2 → Jenkins Agent (Build Node) Install required plugins if needed
Git, Docker, Trivy,Java,SonarQube Scanner , AWS Credentials, kubectl,AWS CLI
Maven/Gradle (depending on project) >> In agent node whichever is need to run the build,install it

SonarQube should NOT be installed on the build node.
Instead:
Run SonarQube on a separate EC2 instance or as a Docker container.
Jenkins only connects to the SonarQube server for code analysis.
